WorldStage Newsonline– United Bank for Africa Plc, a Nigerian pan-African financial services group with subsidiaries in 20 African countries and offices in London, Paris and New York, has announced the approval of the group’s audited financial statements for the half year ended June 30, 2020 at its Board meeting which was held on Thursday, August 13, 2020. In a note to the Nigerian Stock Exchange by Bili A. Odum, Group Company Secretary, the meeting also approved payment of an interim dividend, subject to the approval of the Central Bank of Nigeria. “Further to the above, kindly be advised that the Nigerian Stock Exchange and the investing public would be immediately notified upon receipt of the 2020 Audited Half Year Results & Reports by the Central Bank of Nigeria,” the notice said.